$type$ is evaluated for every type of property that exists, while $slot$ for every slot (maximum 15) in a province.
Abstract value for expansion  of a Property. It’s a sum of all the industries ‘expansion units desire’ of that belong to a property.
Abstract value for shrinkage desire of a Property. It’s a sum of all the industries ‘shrinking units desire’ of that belong to a property.
Amount of food goods needed to maintain a property
Amount of raw goods needed to maintain a property
Amount of industrial goods needed to maintain a property
Value corresponds to the type of industry that exists in that Industry Slot. e.g: Prod_S1 = 1 means wheat industry in slot 1.
Size of the industry that exists in $slot$ (1, 2, 3 up to 15). An industry can exist in 1 and only 1 slot.
Gross Income of an Industry
Costs of an Industry (Labour + Input goods)
How much output of $good$ an industry $slot$ produces. e.g: Prod_S1Sply1 = 2 means slot 1 produces 2 outputs of food(which is good #1)
How much Throughput an industry has
Capable fighting age men (generally available manpower pre politics and taxes) (class = SF, RE, NO, BG, CL)
Actually recruited manpower after politics and taxes  (class = SF, RE, NO, BG, CL)

(1: Food, 2: Salt, 4: Fiber, 5: Fuel, 6: Raw Material, 9: Exotic Goods, 10: Delicacies, 21: Consumer Product, 22: Military Product, 23: Naval Product, 24: Industrial Product, 25: Luxury Product, 32: Commerce, 41: Knowledge, 51: Migration [SPECIAL])
Sector price of a determined good. 1 is food, 24 is industrial, etc
Amount of goods that a province demands. e.g: TN_ProvDmnd1 = 3 means Province demands in total 3 food
